  "prompt": "Which is the shortest completed cricket Test match?",
  "response": "The shortest completed Test match in the history of cricket lasted just **two days**. This remarkable match took place between **Australia and South Africa** in **Durban** from **December 24 to December 25, 1932**.\n\n### Key Highlights:\n\n- **Venue:** Kingsmead Cricket Ground, Durban, South Africa\n- **Duration:** 2 days (December 24-25, 1932)\n- **Result:** Australia won by an innings and 12 runs\n\n### Match Summary:\n\n1. **Australia's First Innings:** Australia batted first and scored 282 runs.\n2. **South Africa's First Innings:** South Africa replied with 199 runs.\n3. **South Africa's Follow-on:** Declared, South Africa only needed to bat once more and were all out for 71 runs in their second innings.\n\nAustralia secured a decisive victory within just two days, making this Test match the shortest in terms of duration. The match was significantly impacted by pitches favoring the bowlers and the overall imbalance between the two teams at that time.\n\n### Notable Factors:\n\n- **Weather Conditions:** The match was affected by rain, which limited the amount of play time.\n- **Team Strengths:** Australia had a stronger side with key bowlers who exploited the pitch conditions effectively.\n\nThis historic match remains a unique instance in Test cricket, highlighting how various factors like weather, pitch conditions, and team dynamics can lead to exceptionally short Test encounters.",
